    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1890-09-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1890-09-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="90"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d90">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Mizner</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Blaine</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Guatemala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date ana="#date_apparent-typo-based-on-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1890-09-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">September</hi> 10, 1891</date>. (Received September
                        25.)</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 161.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to inform you that the bases of
                    peace accepted and agreed upon by Salvador and Guatemala have been now fully
                    complied with. The armies have been withdrawn from their respective frontiers
                    and reduced to a peace footing. Peace will be declared in a few days hence.</p>
                <p>The detailed statement of the bases referred to in my No. 151 is now in the hands
                    of the printers and will not be ready for several days. It was deemed more
                    convenient to have it printed. Copies will be sent to you as soon as possible,
                    followed by translation, if required.</p>
                <p>The settlement gives very general satisfaction, and the diplomatic corps is
                    complimented from all quarters.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing B. Mizner.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
